,Recommended,433950,24040687,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,Dingoes8MeBabies,"Bought this on the Steam sale a couple days ago, and it's already taken a place, alongside Downwell, in the category of games that I play 5 to 20 minutes a day. The game has a very simple but effective design, and the variety of power-ups puts this game above many of its classic counterparts. I also consider this to be on par with Geometry Wars, if not better.Like games such as Downwell, and the great arcade games of the early-mid 80s, this game has an incredible ability to put you ""in the zone"". My first two runs frequently end in the first minute. Then something clicks, I shift into gear, ignore the distractions around me, and I have a...blast. If not a blast, then I grow a big green sword out my front side and swash-buckle them fat space circles.Such a great game."
