,Recommended,433950,23112752,"Posted: 21 May, 2016",all,Ryan Dorkoski,"While I was on the fence aboutBit Blaster XL, the moderately fun (albeit simple) retro gameplay coupled with a price you can't argue with forces me to upvote.This is pure arcade-style gameplay.The only 'permanent' upgrades are unlockable ships that you gain from earning in-game currency. The only real goal is getting a high score.Essentially, the whole game plays on a single scren.If you hit the edge of the screen, you die. The primary mechanic or novelty is the shooting mechanic. While it is toggle-able, you are constantly shooting which obviously depletes ammo stores - which you replenish by pickups dropped when enemies are killed. There are various temporary gun upgrades sort of reminiscent ofContra(not sure why that game comes to mind, but it does).Look, are you going to dump hours and hours into this? Probably not. But for about a buck, you get a pretty wicked game to pass the controller around with friends and try to beat each other's score."
76561198179962105,Recommended,433950,24660724,"Posted: 1 August, 2016",all,silverlunastar39,"For $0.50, this game is well worth the purchase. Is it the best arcade-style shooter? No, but that's okay, because the quality far exceeds the price tag.If you're familiar with Asteroids, then you'll understand this game. Fly through space, shoot stuff, and make that score number grow. That's it.Now, to liven it up a bit, there's a ton of different weapons and ships to unlock and choose from. Pretty cool, right? It is. BBXL isn't perfect, though: the auto-propulsion and turning radius of the ships makes controlling your craft a little difficult. Precision shots are hard to pull off, and when there's a ton of stuff on screen, it can become very difficult to make out exactly what's happening. Adding to all of that is the ammo system, which technically makes sense, and while adding a slight sense of strategy to the game, can become hectic in later parts of the game.But seriously, it's fifty cents on sale. This is a game I can see myself popping on every now and then, determined to break my old high score. And isn't that what the old greats were all about?"
