,Recommended,433950,20875642,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,The Hyper Zone ☣ ✅,"This game is really fun to play and well-designed! It looks like a retro Asteroids-style shooter [and it is] but while remaining simple in concept it is much more sophisticated than it appears.The game is addictive, in a very good way, it keeps you coming back and wanting to be better at playing it. The movement is fluid and the graphics look cool but what stands out to me is the sound design: the music is very good and makes you strive to survive and keep going, the sound effects are perfect, giving you that rewarding feeling when you grab a coin or blow up  stuff. There is enough variety in the ships you unlock to make playing with each a slightly different experience. Game keeps challenging your mind and focus, as you have to watch out for collisions and be careful not to run out of ammo while aiming and controlling the speed. Another plus is the developer seems to be accessible and listening to  feedback.Overall a nice indie title worth more than its price! You might have more fun with this than some overpriced AAA titles."
