,Recommended,433950,24036181,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,Party Lemon,"Due to the recent summer sale, I found myself digging around in the ""cheap cheap"" part of the store and I came across a few titles that I decided to give a try because hey, 49 cents is pretty good for small games. I found Bit Blaster XL. This is a quaint little pixle-based space shooter that throws bullets at you faster and faster over time. You start out with the first basic ship and gain the ability to buy new ones with coins you recieve as drops from kills. There are a nice amount of ships for the game, since the game is so small, you dont really need many anyway. You will be focused on not only your score, but unlocking more ships as well as the achievements the game has to offer. Do i recommend this game? Yes. This game is a nice little time killer that is really addicting when you really get into it. At the time of writing this, the game is on sale for 49 cents but the original price is only 99 cents. I also recommend the game at that price as well. A dollar is a fair price in my opinion for this cute little game. Also, the music is sweet too!"
