,Recommended,433950,20728527,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,Shred,"Wonderful little retro shooter.  Handles like Luftrausers - you only steer your craft left or right, it is always moving forward and always firing.  Enemies drop ammo pickups to replenish your limited ammo (though you always have your basic gun, running out simply takes away your active weapon powerup) and coins which can be spent on new craft.Plays like a mix of Luftrausers and Asteroids with the former's array of different handling craft but a simple, enjoyable gameplay loop where a run can be over in seconds due to a silly mistake, but restarting is very fast for another try.Controls are tight and every death feels like YOUR fault, not the game's.For the price it's fantastic."
,Recommended,433950,23975704,"Posted: 30 June, 2016",all,KidwithSmurf,"*Note: This Review is based off using a PC Keyboard and Mouse for v3.11*Ever play Asteroids back in the day and loved every second of it? Then this game is for you! With its Asteroid style gameplay, you'll be sure to love this! However, even though the game is magnificent there are some slight problems which could be fixed to make it even better which I'll outline in my Pros and Cons below:Pros:♦ Hours of gameplay for the low price of $1 (You definitely get your money's worth)♦ Has Trading Cards♦ Awesome Number of Achievements gotten for just playing the game (You don’t have to do anything special to get these, just play the game)♦ Controls seem to be responsive and work as intended (Pressing the button seems to do what is intended and work very well)♦ Decent variation and number of powerups (Not one powerup seems similar to the last and their seems to be a decent number to always keep the game interesting)♦ Decent variation of enemies (This is decent because  when you progress it doesn’t feel like you are versing the same select enemies over and over again as more types seem to come in the longer you are alive)♦ Nice number of balanced unlockable playable ships♦ Eargasmic Music and Sound Effects that fit the bullet hell scene and make it feel intense whilst you are playing and makes you want to keep playing♦ Graphics are stunning for the genre♦ Everything seems balanced and works off skill more than the power of something (For example, a better ship or weapon upgrade doesn’t always mean you’ll do better, as the game relies on skill)♦ Two modes to suite everyone’s playstyle (Auto-Fire and Non-Auto-Fire which means if you want to really test your skill you can or if you want to casually play you can)♦ Old School look and feel is on point (If you ever played old school pixel, bullet hell games, this is a very good representation. For example, if you played Asteroids, you will love this)♦ Very Good at being both a casual or uncasual game (If you have spare time and just want to casually play something this game works perfectly or if you want to go for a highscore and beat your friends this works perfectly too)♦ Difficulty seems scaled correctly (I say this as the longer you play the harder it gets without being too easy at the start or too hard at the end. It feels like you ease into harder stages without actually realising which is decent)♦ PC Option Menu that seems to work (Decent for what it is)♦ Remapable controls (This is amazing as we can easily and quickly change the keys to whatever button we want)Cons:♦ No incentive to switch powerups unless needing extra ammo (This is annoying as I didn’t really feel ammo was a problem and some powerups suited me better than others, so why switch?)♦ Powerups don’t stack (This seems weird as I would have thought that collecting more than one of the same powerup would have stacked and upgraded it to a certain point, instead collecting more more than one of the same powerup only gives you ammo and nothing else)♦ Some people who don’t like this gamestyle may find it very repetitive (This is because there is no levels and not much variation from each time you click play)♦ Steam highscores don't seem to go off mode or ship (This is really bad as someone can play any ship and auto-fire and be registered on Steam with the same score as someone who played non-auto-fire. Steam highscores should be done like ingame highscores by fire mode and ship)Overall, the game is one of the best Pixelated, Old School, Bullet Hell games that I’ve ever played on Steam. Even though there are lots of cons, the pros still outweigh the cons as the cons are only minor things which I believe would help improve the game. Therefore, if you like Old School games like Asteroids, then you’ll love this and at the low price of $1.00, you can’t go wrong!PS: It also seems the Developers read the reviews, which is good. I had listed in my Cons things like obvious Steam highscores hacking and no PC resolution mode. Since listing these in my Cons the obviously hacked highscores have been removed and a PC resolution mode has been added. Amazing game and amazing Developers!"
