76561198166771313,Recommended,433950,30915698,Posted: 2 April,all,dstreet319,"A great throwback to the old arcade games like Galaga and many others.Bit Blaster XL takes place on one screen with and endless onslaught of enemies that keeps getting more intense over time. You can pick up weapons that each have different variety just like in Contra. You can unlock more ships that have different play styles like more speed, smaller/bigger, and more health. You can also pick up health/shields and boosters that used when you speed up or slowing down. My only complaint is weapons you pick up will replace the one you are currently using so it won't matter if you pick it up by accident.Rating: 9/10"
76561198194763051,Recommended,433950,32209281,Posted: 5 June,all,matthew.orenstein3000,"It's funny how arcade games are no longer a booming business. Two decades ago they were all the rage. And this game reminds me of those years. Bit Blaster XL is a throwback in every way. Shooting for points? Check. Powerups? Check. Methods to rack up high scores? Check. Gimmick to keep you comming back? You betcha. This games gimmick is simple. Your ship is on auto-pilot both in acceleration and shooting. You move left and right as well as use turbo and brakes, although you will never stop dead unless you die. You also have an ammo meter that you must build up with pellets enemies drop. Unlockable ships, plenty of power-ups, and retro sound and feel? yeah I recommend this. At $0.99 it's a steal."
