,Recommended,433950,28251191,"Posted: 8 December, 2016",all,Erikek,"This is a nice little game to play when your bored, it is fairly simple, and it is more of a casual game, but it can still have a challenging side to it. It has pixelated graphics (the good type of pixelated graphics), and different music for each different space ship. I'm personally a sucker for any game with unlockable characters/abilities and powerups, this game has both. Also, the game has a variety of ways to control the spaceship; the mouse, arrows, wasd, and you can use controllers, this is a nice little touch so that anyone can play the game the way they please. Overall, I liked this game, there are a few downsides though; even with the powerups the gameplay is very simple, making it repetitive. The controls are good, but the way the spaceship works isn't as good, you can't strafe, you can only shoot where your moving towards and you can't stop your spaceship, although you can slow it down. I think adding completely different game modes, and in those new game modes adding a different movement system could help make the game better.The game is relatively cheap. I would recommend this game to casual gamers, people with a thirst for high scores, or people that just don't have a lot of time on their hands and just wanna play for a bit."
