,Recommended,433950,20953325,"Posted: 4 February, 2016",all,seem,"Hi.I LOVE spaces hooters. Bit Blaster XL is a mix of Asteroids, Robotron and Berzerk. Camera is over the space room full of enemies. You have a spaceship with limited ammo. The trick is: better weapons needs more ammo. Even without combo point system you had to destroy someting constantly, because every dead enemy drops ammo and you need it to feed a weapon. If you're out of ammo, you're back to a standard pew pew laser.It's a very simple, but effective mechanic. It's always risk vs reward, so you can play safe, or beat a crap out of hi-score. Game is really hard, because most weapons shoots only in the direction that you are flying (like in Berzerk), but enemies of course are all over you and can aim. So it is a challenge, like any other arcade style shooter, but not unfair and I feel I can handle it.Have fun.---------------------------------------------------------------EDIT: Last upgrade is really nice. More powerups (including new shelds), ability to speed up, enemies respawns more often. I feel I'm dying much faster, but scoring faster, too."
