,Recommended,433950,20841756,"Posted: 29 January, 2016",all,xd,"You are the newest pilot in a specially trained devision of the army trained to fly rocketships. You are one of the last lines of defense that your planet has. You step in the rocket and see the platform slowly move further away from you. And then you see them. The asteroids. You start firing at them, destroying them and defending earth as much as you can. You see your first support from earth in a glowing, colorful ball. You fly your ship towards it, to find out it is an upgrade for your gun. You install it and find out its power. After a while, earth asks you to start collecting coin-like alien material that, once back down on earth, can be used to upgrade your ship. Sometime later, you send a packet of about 5 coins down to earth, and in return you get another ship. Smaller, faster, it has faster firing capabilites and is better in many ways. You defend earth with all your might, recieving support in the form of new spaceships and gun upgrades when you see the aliens ships firing towards you. You start firing towards them too, trying to dodge the asteroids as much as you can. As you slowly become more focused on the situation, you start to find out how to fly effectively and how to dodge asteroids to only focus on the spaceships. You realize your entire team has been taken out by the aliens.You are earth's last hope.You are the Bit Blaster.(That was a story I wrote for the plot of the game: don't presume it is official, that is just what I like to imagine it being :])Overall, this is a very good game for its value. It has great music, is a decent difficulty and has a lot of features that take a little bit of time to learn. Overall, it is simple but has great mechanics and is a rewarding experience when you finally reach the drop. I highly recommend this game to a lot of people, especially those who like the game Asteroids (the arcade game, you know)"
