76561198099704746,Recommended,433950,20954696,"Posted: 4 February, 2016",all,Terrahex,"Bit Blaster isn't the best game out there, but it's fun enough that I got about an additional hour of enjoyment out of it for the purposes of this re-reveiw (see below for old reveiw).While many of my old criticisms still stand, the recent update done by the developer Nickervision added enough new content that I found it more worthwhile to play (now on my newly unlocked fourth ship which I quickly came to prefer over the previous three).Much of the combat is as I described before, but I'd like to reiterate how the powerups are the best part of this game. They often change the way the game is played in ways both large and small. with some, the best strategy is to be calm and fire conservatively like with the blue explosive power up, while with others, the best strategy is to spray and pray, like with the richocheting pink power up. I quickly found ones that I prefered. My favorite was always the purple one that acted like a short range shot gun.Of course, minor critisisms became more pronounced the longer I played. It's often very easy to take multiple hits in quick succession for ships with shields due to the lack of invinsibility frames. The scoreboard is pretty meaningless and hard to get to considering this is a game where the only goal is to get a high score.In fact, after a while, the game gets pretty samey. Since the score is such an after thought, the only reason to play the game is for the game's own sake. Once every round of bit blasting feels like the last one, it starts to get boring. After the first few ship unlocks, it takes too long to get the next ship for that to be a proper motivation to keep playing.Still, for all it's faults, I had a decent ammount of fun with it. For the price of a dollar, I think it's worth a try, especially if it's on sale.------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Ship combat is not Bit Blaster's strength. Bullets only eject from the front of the ship, and the ship can only go forward with an incredibly large turning radius. It's clunky. That's not to say that you can't get good at it, it's just not fun to get good at.What is Bit Blaster XL's strength then? well, it has some kick♥♥♥♥♥music. That alone kept me going for longer than I would normally have.I think the real strength of Bit Blaster is its power up system. Each power up is completely unique and has the potential to be completely game changing. Sure, there are the mundane ones that just make you fire faster or also shoot from your butt, but there are also the ones that make large balls the same size as your ship bounce off the walls of the screen, filling the entire thing with your bullets, or the ones that make explosives that blow up everything in front of your ship, or the one that gives you a short range laser that makes you have to get up in the business of anythin you want to kill.They're pretty sweet, I'll admit.Still, it's not enough to carry the game for me. The terrible controls really hinder the game, and the space ships that I unlocked before quitting were pretty lack luster. Maybe someone else will find it more fun than I did."
