,Recommended,433950,22656515,"Posted: 26 April, 2016",all,HEY!!!,"I had some negative criticism about this game at first, and although some of the problems I have with it still stand, The dev Nickervision has been extremely cool about taking my critique seriously and adding things to the game based on my suggestions. That's something I've never ever experienced before, so props to him.As for the game its a pretty simple score attack asteroids clone with some interesting powerups, a little variation in enemies, a few different ships, and some pretty jammin music.The game is fun to play as a casual arcade game, and for $1 you can't beat the value, so I'd recommend it. However there are a few areas where I think this game falls short / could be improved.-Overall the game feels very slow. I’m sure some users like this / are used to this and so I do not necessarily think it has to be changed for the main game mode, but I personally like fast paced games, and I would like a ""Hard Mode"" or ""Super Speed"" mode where everything is faster, your ship, the enemies and how fast the enemies appear on screen. Also I think the biggest difficulty is how cramped the screen gets when it fills up with enemies, for this new mode it would be cool to see the screen expanded so you had more movement space.-There is not too much diversity in what you are shooting at, I have not gotten too far so there may be more enemies later, but the game is hard enough that you will spend most of your time shooting at circles and the occasional ship before dying and starting over. Since I'm going to be spending most of my time in the first part of the game it should be engaging.-The powerups still feel a little lacking to me, some suggestions I have for new ones are: lightning, plasma beam, multiple guided missiles, sin wave ray? My favorite powerups are the lightsaber and the one that shoots energy bombs, because they feel unique, the rest are just slight variations on the starting gun.-With powerups I would also like to see some kind of tier or upgrade system. players want to be able to upgrade their weapons and hopefully be overpowered, this could be implemented in another mode perhaps where along with ammo dead enemies also drop another type of pickup that upgrades your current weapon if you pick up enough. Also I think primary and secondary upgrades should be separate, you should be able to have the shield or magnet with another weapon.-The coin system feels lacking, I would rather pick up 20 coins per run and need 500 to get the next ship than maybe pick up 1 coin and only need 10. If i play a round and get no coins, it feels unsatisfying, also different tiers of coins would be fun, red, blue green, and different values for each-The main upgrade system could also be reworked, buying new ships is nice, and I know you cant have too much change due to the leaderboards, but as a player I would like to be able to permanently upgrade my ship or have some external options to use my coins and feel like I have a sense of progression.In closing: More enemy variation, crazier powerups, more upgrades, and a sense of progression would all be additions that would make what is already a good game into something with more replayability and addictiveness."
