76561198119369929,Recommended,433950,32908745,Posted: 27 June,all,Lex,"What a perfect little space shooter! Don't let the cheap price convince you that this is shovelware. Bit Blaster XL is a great deal of fun.Imagine Asteroids, except that you control a more maneuverable ship that constantly moves forward, and you face a wider variety of hostile ships that shoot at you.You can unlock additional ships with slightly different stats (shield count, bomb count, movement speed, hitbox size). Although the ships are all the same basic white palette, and all look kind of similar, they handle differently enough that each one feels like it requires a distinct play style. The game stores separate high scores for each ship, too. The one drawback is that ships must be unlocked in order, meaning you'll have to play for quite some time before you uncover the V8.Unlockables are purchased using coins that downed enemies and asteroids drop at random during play. This can be a pain, as there are times when you can play for a while without making any progress toward a new ship. On the plus side, finding these collectibles can make even a poor scoring run feel worthwhile, since they bring you that much closer to your next unlockable.Sessions can last anywhere from a minute to an hour, depending on how well you play. I find that it lines up with my attention span pretty well. Generally, this game is good for a quick round or two while you're procrastinating.I highly recommend this game if you're a fan of space shooters, or are looking for a cheap, fast game to pad your collections of achievements and trading cards."
