76561198213565660,Recommended,433950,22306806,"Posted: 8 April, 2016",all,Xanpheon,"TL:DR - Short and sweet. Classic asteroidy action. Good fun.Now for the real review.Bit Blaster XL is a retro arcadey Asteroids-esque game. It's an incredibly well executed fast paced bullet hell, with a catchy arcade soundtrack and unlockables. Whats not to like?It takes a while to get used to the controls, simple as they are, so be prepared to smash into the walls a lot. There are a large number of upgrades to choose from, although they could be more accurately described as powerups given they appear at random. That said, without experience it is hard to tell what powerup does what, or even which ones would be useful. The fact that some of the powerup sprites are only differentiated by colour is not helpful, so be prepared also to spend a fair chunk of time swearing because you let the amazing Explosion powerup go for the terrible version of the shotgun powerup (for example).The game also swiftly gets incredibly cluttered, although as I said this is a bullet hell game so what were you expecting. For this there are several useful powerups and several not so useful. Heres a list of my top 5 and one I never take, even if it means sticking with the peashooter they give you at the start.(Note: These are all my own names, given the lack of andy form of guide)1.) Explosion/Lightsaber (Blue E and Green L respectively) depending on which ship you use. Fast ships go for lightsaber as a swift turn can cut through the bigass splitting asteroids really quickly, netting you a nice chunk of ammo. Otherwise go for the explosion, as it lingers for a bit and any enemies that walk into the field left  blow up too.2.) Don't get me wrong, both of the above are incredibly useful on any ship, it's just that faster ships perform better with the lightsaber than slower ones.3.) Homing balls (Orange H). This fires (at a cost of 5 ammo) an orange blob at a random enemy on screen, and lets you keep firing the standard gun. Useful, and given that each ammo drop gives you 5 ammo, as  long as you're quick enough this can go on forever.4.) Ricochet (sorry can't remember the icon for this one). As the name says. Very useful, especially later, as there is no way they can miss with the number of enemies on screen.5.) I agonized for a bit over this one, because there are a couple that are really good. But the last one is Multi (Orange M). This fires a shot to the front and the back. This is especially useful given the turning circle of some of the ships.The one you should never, ever, ever go for :-M♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ (Purple M). The only boost this has, as far as I can tell, is making the ammo pickups drift towards you slightly quicker. Given that they do this anyway, and that it slows down the speed of your main weapon firing, it's just useless. Unless you want a challenge."
