,Recommended,433950,24070007,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,iie-kyo,"""I am just learning to make games."" the exit screen says.Sir, you've figured out how to make games that are fun down to its very core - the gameplay.  Incredibly enjoyable - old school Asteroids playstyle.  You have limited ammo - that ammo can be obtained from the enemies you destroy on screen.  Random powerups spawn and give you all sorts of fun enhancements - bouncing bullets, shotguns, behind-the-back attacks, bombs, etc.  You just keep playing until you die and keep trying to make the highest score.Unlike Asteroids you are always moving and can only slow your ship down at the cost of using your boost meter.  If you run out of ammo you're left vulnerable so always keep track of how much you have left.  Different weapons use different amounts of ammo.I look forward to seeing more from this author.  Stick with this formula Adam, you understand what a lot of us gamers want - addicting and fun gameplay.Seriously, if you see it on sale, get it, but get it anyway if it's not.  You can do far worse with a buck.  I absolutely love these types of ""here's the gameplay, have fun"" sorta games."
