76561198057243740,Recommended,433950,29051102,Posted: 5 January,all,Skrilla,"What is Bit Blaster XLBit Blaster XL is a retro arcade game inspired by games like Asteroids and Galaga. You play as one of eight unlockable ships and destroy asteroids and enemy space ships to gain points while using numerous upgrades.GameplayThe gameplay is simple but it works in its favor. The weapon upgrades are mostly unique and almost always useful(The exception being the Trail power up). You can use bombs to clear the entire screen of enemies. Coins randomly drop from enemies and you can use them to buy a total of eight different ships. The coins drop so often that I unlocked seven of the eight ships within 2.5 hours of playing. The ships have four stats: Life, Speed, Firing Speed, and Number of Bombs. Each ship is unique and plays differently from each other. The game also controls amazingly well on the Steam Controller and I highly recommend you use it if you own one. My one big criticism is that the game does become repetitive after a couple hours.The VisualsWhile it doesn't look stunning, it doesn't need to be since it is a retro arcade throwback. They graphics do their job and do it well.ConclusionOverall a good game with few flaws but it can get repetitive after awhile. This game is definetly worth your $.99."
