,Recommended,433950,23349960,"Posted: 2 June, 2016",all,Queen,"Genuinly one of the best shmup's I've ever played. The fantastic pixel art blends perfectly with the really catchy music that chirps away as you blast astriods and enemy spaceships.The sense of progression is simple, as it should be in this retro style game, and doesn't feel overwhelmingly grindy - although it is essentially what you're doing. The weapons really stand out too - Some are your average three-way bullets, or your slightly bigger ones - but there are some really intuitive weapons too. My personal favourite is the lazor sword, which is bloody perfect as long as you manage your ammo.Oh - This game also has ammo. Yeah, it's an odd mechanic to add into an endless shooter like this, but it works really well. You can have your shooting set to automatic, which is really handy when you just want to focus on getting out of annoying situations, but I prefer to play with this turn off. One addition that I feel would really help the game feel much smoother would be the ability to toggle this function on and off during a game - Maybe binding it to 'Y' or 'B' on the controller? That way, one can switch their focus from gaining points and swerving to dodge the debris that quickly fills your screen.Overall, if you think you like the look of this, you'll probably have tonnes of fun with it. And why not? It's under £1~-Ashe"
