76561198021868661,Recommended,433950,23440235,"Posted: 7 June, 2016",all,Insomnia'77,"""I think I'm going to play World of T... No, wait! There's a new update for BIT Blaster! Again!""This review is for the version 2.10 of the game.Graphics: 30%Audio: 30%Gameplay: 60%Replayability: 80%Value for money: 100%Overall: 60%About the scores: In shoot'em ups/bullet hell, I feel the visual- and audio presentation is as important as the gameplay. You need a catchy tune and some real cool graphics to really get the adrenaline pumping. That is why I weight all 5 scores similar.The first time I played this game, I was not impressed, to say the least. The graphics were dull, the music did not fit the game, and the sound effects needed work. This is still the case. The gameplay was not very engaging, and the controls were not optimal. That, on the other hand has changed... a lot!And maybe the constant changes and additions is what makes me play this game over and over again. Even though I gave it such a low score. Because, as a game, I feel the price tag is about right. You get your moneys' worth. It might be engaging for 10 minutes. Then you put it away and forget about it. Unless you try to unlock all the ships. But since I wrote the intial review, the developer has been in constant dialogue with me, improving the parts that me and the other players pointed out. Implementing ideas, and makes the game evolve over time. That is very interesting to be a part of. Personally, I feel Steam is not the arena for developing a game. I require a finished product, when I buy something from steam. But that time is probably in the past.So what do you get if you buy this game? It's a shoot'em up with simple graphics. The controls are tight. The ships have diffrent stats, but not much more different than that. It's a single difficulty/level with increasing numbers of enemies over time. And powerups. A lot of different powerups.I would reccomend this game to anyone that likes shoot'em ups/bullet hells. I must admit that I have pressed the play ""again button"" too many times. Just to get a better score. Because I know I can do better the next time."
