,Recommended,433950,28788368,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,ZHDINC,"At $0.99 (or cheaper if on sale), you can't do much better for a retro-styled arcade shmup. The game plays much like Asteroids except you can't cross the borders of the screen and the enemies only come from the left and right sides. The game starts off with simple asteroids to pick off and gradually introduces enemies of increasing complexity as your score increases. Initially, there is only one ship to play the game, but as you gather coins from random drops from destroyed enemies, there are seven additional variants to unlock (but only in order). The late game ships are generally more capable, so most players will probably be sticking with Ships 6-8. I personally prefer Ship 8 because it has the best capabilities, but at 100 coins to unlock (in addition to needing to using coins to unlock the previous ships), you'll have to play for a while to get it.There are a multitude of powerups to collect during regular gameplay, but I think most will find that only a few are actually useful and the others are quite terrible. Now, it is tempting for me to just write off the offending powerups, but it does make for interesting gameplay in that you are trying to dodge enemies and bullets in addition to powerups that are likely to ruin a good run. It can be agony waiting for the right powerup to appear sometimes though (especially near the start, I tend to start over if a powerup I don't like appears first). After you get a powerup, you have it as long as you don't run out of ammo. It can be really difficult to conserve ammo with auto-fire enabled, but quite simple to do firing manually.Two of powerups have rather odd behavior though. There is a homing powerup that seems to go after ships you are aiming at (otherwise targeting closest ships), which is fine, but this often means that you'll have a homing shot going after a small asteroid in the distance while completely ignoring actual threats nearby. You can still fire manually with the homing powerup, but it is frustrating to watch the homing shot completely pass more dangerous enemies. The other powerup that I feel has issues is magnet, a powerup that draws in ammo and coins on screen. There is really no need for this powerup in manual firing mode, but the thing I really don't like about it is the lag it seems to introduce with firing inputs (which is hard to tell if it's intentional or not). I have accidentally collided with a number of enemies due to a lack of firing from this lag that the magnet powerup seems to introduce. Though again, this just adds to gameplay in giving me an incentive to avoid collecting the magnet powerup altogether.Aside from powerups, my only other real gripe is that sometimes the hitbox seems bigger than it should be, but otherwise gameplay is about what you can expect from an arcade shmup styled in way that feels like Asteroids. There are a number achievements with the game that most will find are appropriately difficult. I still haven't gotten the 75K in a single run achievement, but will as I try to improve my high score.And on the topic of high scores, this is a gripe that is unrelated to the game itself. When I first played the game, the Version 3.00 patch was relatively new and the leaderboards had scores that appeared achievable. However, I recently checked and the top scores are now clearly the work of cheaters. The main way you can tell is that they unlocked all the achievements in the game within an hour (most within fifteen minutes) which just reeks of foul play. On a game worth $0.99, come on, really? Is it really that important to you to cheat to get the highest score on the leaderboard? I mostly play to improve my own score, but it is sad that not even this game is immune to cheaters unfairly getting the top positions on the scoreboard. Unfortunate, but I think most will be able to see where the real leaderboard starts. EDIT: Most recent check has the blatantly cheating scores removed, so at least for a moment there is a proactive effort going on to keep the leaderboard clean.Get this game! It is a load of fun! I personally turn off the music in favor of my own. I recommend playing with a controller."
