,Recommended,433950,28931132,Posted: 1 January,all,Keeehort,"Fun, addictive, retro styled shooter. Can't get enough of this game! And for 50 cents! Not to mention the soundtrack, 10/10. Amazing game for the price, would recommend to anyone. You'll never get sick of this game, or the sound track. Definentally would recommend to anyone for full price, even though I got it on the winter sale. This game is wonderful. The gameplay, which is basically just running around in circles shooting balls that drop ammo, gets harder as the game progresses. Enemies start to appear, which shoot rockets at you. You start of with a shield, and after one hit, its gone. Then, if you take another hit, your done. You have to restart. Which, honestly, doesn't get repetitive, surprisingly. I've only gotten to around 4k score myself. There are many powerups in this game, such as a lightsaber to whack through the big balls, or grenades that spurt out little balls on impact. And, a little cool feature, coins that drop as you get farther in the game. With these coins, you can unlock different space ships. (You can't buy coins either, which is amazing. You actually have to play to unlock more space ships, which I think is a great feature. Non pay 2 win.) This game; I just can't get enough of it. 10/10, a fun retro style shooter that doesn't get old."
