76561198201666099,Recommended,433950,29017403,Posted: 4 January,all,Otis,"Blast off!There are many retro-esque games that merely mimic the art style, having gameplay that wasn't possible for the time, overdetailed models, and complicated controls. They don't have believable worlds and couldn't be on an 80's console due to the size. Retro games were all about simple games and concepts put into many levels.Bit Blaster XL is amazing in creating the illusion that you're playing on an NES. The graphics are on point with the pixel theme, the music feels like an upgraded version of that of ""Space Invaders"", and the gameplay is golden.In this game, you take control of a pixel spaceship, your goal is to destroy the enemy fleet which is invading your territory. You do this by collecting one of many powers to help you destroy astroids and ships. But be carefull! If you fly into the edge of the map you instantly die.Thoughts and OpnionsIn conclusion, Bit Blaster XL is a game that everybdy with over 15 minutes of time should play. I give Bit Blaster XL a score of 9.5/10, with the title of ""Fit for an arcade; an instant classic""."
