,Recommended,433950,29874167,Posted: 12 February,all,Sammy_is_confused,"Bit Blaster XL is good bit of casual fun. Reminds me of Super Crate Box a little bit. Very simple mechanics, very addictive, very, very affordable. You can make back most (if not all) of the price of the game easily by selling off Inventory cards obtained from playing it, it's that cheap.The music is catchy and I like that the background music changes with each new unlocked ship. It gives the player a reason to get enough coins to unlock one other than a different ship sprite and slightly different stats.I really like that there is such a variety of content in such a simple game. Lots of different enemies, obstacles and powerups. My favourite powerups are the Fire/Laser ones(they act pretty similar to each other), the Homing one, and the Exploding one. The Magnet one is entirely detrimental in my opinion, however I don't think that having negative powerups is a bad thing, it makes avoiding them a challenge plus it gives you a reason to use the bombs, as it removes them from the screen.I didn't find much use for Autofire mode, I prefer to aim manually and only shoot when I think I'm on target rather than constantly spraying bullets.I think it would be really cool if the different ship types had mechanics entirely unique to each other; for example, different default firing type/rate, or the amount of ammo the ship can hold at once.Definitely worth a play, especially at the price of a toilet roll."
