,Recommended,433950,32342448,Posted: 11 June,all,a_gep,"""A throwback to the classic quarter eating arcade games of the 80's. Bit Blaster XL is a retro styled, addictive, and fast paced arcade shoot 'em up!""This line from the description tells it all. A truly awesome game!It feels like the love child of the classic Asteriods and Geometry Wars with a bit more influence from the former. If you like this genre you'll find a true gem playing this.The game plays smoothly, I haven't tried the controller as I prefer the keyboard for these kind of games. The 8bit style chiptunes are nice. All the different enemies have a distinct behaviour and attack method, there are a wide range of powerups: you'll like some of them and try avoid the others depending on your play style.The author has put a lot of work and love into this piece, and it shows. There are small but important details like the warning stipes at the edge of the screen before an enemy appears, and the fact that you can retry after dying with a single click; exactly how a game like this should be done!As others said, the game is simple but hard to master, and strangely addictive.I costs around 1 USD and it's worth every penny. I am looking forward to see other quality games from the author!"
