,Recommended,433950,32537571,Posted: 18 June,all,TheRedTetra,"EDIT: Updated from a No to Yes recommendation.BackgroundI am not a fan of arcade shooters. However, I bought this game because it was under a dollar (in terms of USD), and I haven't played arcade shooters in more than a decade. So it was more of a novelty.OverviewBit Blaster XL itself is not very innovative. It's a pretty straightforward arcade shooter, with a grindy unlock system for more powerful spaceships. Ironically I preferred the slower, lower-tier spaceship for its easier control haha.I find the difficulty ramp-up a little unsatisfying. Some spaceships are mere annoyances, while there's 2 particular spaceships that are a must-kill or the map becomes a dodge-em after than a shoot-em-up.Ammo and Boost/Brake is a limited resource, though the latter is time-rechargeable. The limited ammo is pretty interesting, though I find it a little on the tough side to conserve ammo given that all the Ammo powerups eat through ammo so quickly.For its price, Bit Blaster XL is pretty alright for a quick, casual play. There's enough gameplay mechanics and polish inside to give you a few good hours spread over a couple of days.MusicEach ship has its own music. I think my spaceship choice is somewhat related to my preferred choice of tunes. It's a little refreshing when you switch to a new ship after a couple of rounds/days and you hear a new tune.ControlsI highly recommend using a controller for this game. If you're using controller, you should probably remap the buttons so that you can Fire, Boost/Brake at the same time.PerformanceThis game has mild performance issues. Keep VSync on. Although VSync off makes the controls more responsive, but it causes random screen stutters. I'm using i7-7700HQ so it's not a spec issue.Overall* Polish: 5/5* Novelty: 2/5* Music: 4/5* Fun: 4/5* Replayability: 5/5* Playtime: 0.2 - 0.5 hour eachSee Also: Orbt XLGo get the developer's other game as a Bundle: Orbt XL. It's more addictive and fun."
