76561198079351541,Recommended,433950,20758937,"Posted: 25 January, 2016",all,Coggo,"Bit blaster XL is a surprisingly addictive, classic retro arcade style themed space shooter. Don't expect to be sinking thousands of hours into this game, but it is a great throwback to the times of playing on arcade machines. It has a very cool and fitting soundtrack, and offers a solid amount of game time for $1.00. The one major downfall to this game is that it does not take long to unlock all of the available ships. After this, there is nothing else the game really has to offer besides constantly trying to beat your highscore.TL;DRThis game is a fun, 8-bit space shooter with super simple controls, cool things to unlock as you ""progress"" in the game, super cheap price and great if you have some spare time, however it is lacking in large amounts of replayability, and will really only allow an hour or two of gameplay before the player may get bored.8/10"
