76561197981362890,Recommended,433950,28674589,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,dirahl,"Mindless fun, but don't play on a Mac without a controller.It's a dollar worth of fun (although I got it at 51% off--WOW!).  I can play it while I'm watching TV, which is nice.   I'm sure it would be better on a Windows machine with a controller.  I played it on a Mac (since that's all I have while I'm away), and the controls are utter crap without a joystick.  I can't use the arrow keys and shoot at the same time, probably because the firing key is Control.  And unbeknownst to me, control + left arrow on a Mac takes you to the dashboard--even in the middle of the game!  And you have to press Control + Option to fire a bomb, because that key is Alt, which is much more accessible on a Windows machine than on a Mac.What that basically means is I'm stuck using the ""autofire"" mode, which is still fun enough, but much harder to sustain as you progress.  Especially when you get those sweet ships with the fast rate of fire.  On autofire mode, those ships aren't very useful since they run out of ammo so fast.  I don't think I'll be able to progress much more without a controller.All of this wouldn't be an issue if we were allowed to designate new keys for the functions.  Please?"
