,Recommended,433950,21123928,"Posted: 11 February, 2016",all,Flying Shisno,"A great little arcade games where you fly around, steering left and right(you're always moving forward), speed boosting, and shooting, since your ship is always shooting without your input. This game is really fun and simple. There are plenty of weapon pickups with unique attacks, my favorite being the beam, though it has the trade off of being short.There are unlockable ships too, with varying size, shooting speed, move speed, and shields, which determines how many hits you can take before death, though crashing into a wall will always insta-kill you.As you play the game, little gold coins will either drop from enemies, or simply roll on screen. Collect them and use them to unlock the ships. First ship unlock costs 5 points, next one costs 10, and they keep increasing in cost by 5, with the current(as of this review) final ship costing 30.This game is just incredibly fun and for only a dollar at most. I definitely recommend it."
