,Recommended,433950,28807155,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,LAMBDACHI,"Bit Blaster XL is an outstanding PC rebuild of the mobile game Bit Blaster (redundancy much?). This game is quite literally Asteroids ON STEROIDS!With all of these newer games being driven by graphics and story, it's a breath of fresh air to see a game that hearkens back to the golden age of games where the only thing that mattered was getting as high of a score as you could. And that is exactly what the dev wanted from Bit Blaster XL.The minimalist art style further extends the feeling that you are playing a quarter-eating arcade game from the 80's, along with simple controls that could be played on even an NES controller, short rounds for quick sessions, and competing for high scores with other players.And now for my big question: For this game, would you rather pay a quarter per-round, or a dollar for as many rounds as you'd like? I'd choose the latter. Seriously, this game is only one dollar; a steal of a deal considering how well-made this game really is. Don't wait for a sale, BUY IT NOW!"
