76561198143746424,Recommended,433950,33489972,Posted: 12 July,all,nishunia,"I checked out the reviews before buying this and I noticed that a few users described the game as ""addictive"". I didn't take this seriously until I downloaded the game for myself and started playing it. Every single time I 'die', I convince myself that I'll have ""just one more round"", which naturally turns into several more.When I think of retro-styled games, I usually think of irritating beeping and booping noises. 'Bit Blaster XL' doesn't punish you with that. There's an awesome soundtrack that only adds to the addictive experience; I don't get sick and tired of the music at all, even when I'm retrying the same level for the dozenth time in a row.Finally, the controls are simple and easy to learn. I've been playing with a Logitech controller and the game works perfectly with it. I haven't tried playing with the keyboard, but I don't think I want to when I've found that the controller is very responsive."
