76561197996179340,Recommended,433950,22306351,"Posted: 8 April, 2016",all,Yotarian,"Absolutely love it!Do you like Asteroids?  Do you like Luftrausers?  This game is a great blend of the two, with the classic feel of blowing up space debris but with a variety of ships and powerups to help you along the way.  The gameplay is very engaging, and when you inevitably die, you get pulled right back in for another round.On top of that, the sound track is incredible, and changes with each ship!  Each track has a lively beat that ramps up as you play, and fits very well with the fast paced nature of the game.Something that I really appreciate in this game, that so many others of this genre don't have, is the ability to toggle auto-fire.  The constant ""pew-pew-pew"" of similar games can feel repetitive and grating, but Bit Blaster lets you decide which mode you would prefer when you select your ship.  There are also separate high scores for each ship, and for each fire mode as well!For less money (and calories) than a dollar menu sandwich, Bit Blaster XL is an absolute riot of a good time!"
