76561198076455611,Not Recommended,433950,30215247,Posted: 27 February,all,Phantom Gamer,"I want to like this game. I want to like it so badly, but there are a few things that hold it back, at least for me.Chief among them is the controls. I like my ships to go where I point, not rotate how I tell them. I'm comparing this game to Geometry Wars: Retro Evolved, and if the movement of the ship was handled like it was in that game I'd enjoy it a lot more -- especially since it would make aiming much easier. I guess it comes down to the disign choice where your ship can't stop moving -- I see the complexity it adds, but even if there was a way to make a control stick correspond to which direction the ship was facing it would be mch appreciated. The other things I dislike -- like a lack of wraparound -- are largely a matter of taste and don't affect my experience that badly, but the controls really hold this game back.As far as the positives go, the other reviews are largely correct when they sing this game's praises. For the ridiculously low price point, having that many different ships and weapons is downright insane. There's a lot here, and I really want to dig into it further, but without any way to change the controls it may be stuck on the shelf for quite some time.That said, if this game is on sale it becomes stupid cheap, and it's still inexpensive on its own, so if you want to spend a buck on steam, there are worse ways.All in all, promising game with huge potential undone by controls that, while they do what they're supposed to, work against the tight maneuverability these sorts of games are known for. The low, low price point redeems a lot o the flaws, but since I still won't be getting much enjoyment out of it, I have to give it a thumbs down."
