76561198200700174,Not Recommended,433950,33209156,Posted: 3 July,all,*****,"I can't see why this has so many positive reviews and so few negative ones.  Rather than being comparable to arcade classics like Asteroid and Space Invaders, it's a pretty average free-to-play mobile game, like an uninspired Tilt To Live clone, up on Steam for some reason.The good:  Responsive, not buggy, there's a game here with an element of skill.  Graphics and sfx are simple, but appealing.  Seems well-programmed and highly compatible.  Occupies your attention if you need to kill time.The bad:  Unoriginal.  Slow, dull start.  Awkward control scheme, without enjoyable movement physics (space-themed graphics, but drives like a car).  Success seems more based on randomness than skill, due to random power ups and enemies.  No real depth.  Skinner-box unlockables.  Music is an earworm that gets old fast.Bottom line: It's not like it's crushingly terrible, and it's certainly not expensive, but why spend time playing this with so many other options?"
