76561198028334790,Not Recommended,433950,24680163,"Posted: 2 August, 2016",all,Samurai Jack,"A fun game for a very short while, then it got frustrating and very not fun once I got into it.The powerup system is poorly thought out. There are far too many powerups that I constantly find myself pausing to see which one is which. Most of the powerups are bad and others are overpowered. Lack of upgrades or a coherant pattern of weapon scheme makes it so that your score is luck of the draw. Then when you get a weapon that you like, you spend your time trying to avoid other weapons floating around. Then if you accidentally hit one, it's a major detriment.It's a cell phone game and it shows. Twin stick would make this game a lot more fun. Steering left and right like there are wheels on the ground literally makes no sense, a rocket can't move like that. Without twin stick, it's just frustrating to navigate around the enemies that shoot directly at you and you find yourself just moving around in circles. The arbitrary turning radius is also difficult to get used to.The automatic firing mode is poorly balanced and once you get down to zero bullets which is all too easy in the slow earlier sections, then you just constantly lose your powerups."
