 mom, Anna, become bored with her suffocating marriage to Karenin. We see her cheat on her husband with the handsome, virile Vronsky, and thus, her family gets destroyed (via her quest for a non-boring life). And by the end of the near-800-page, exquisitely-written novel, we see Anna fall deep into depression with Vronsky, with whom she has moved in. We see her spiral into an existential quagmire, one from which she cannot escape. Except by one method.And what does Bit Blaster XL allow us to see?Nothing!Compared to Tolstoy’s classic, Bit Blaster XL is a Mass Grave—mere seizure-inducing lights appearing on a screen, set to the tune of blindfolded men screaming.Bit Blaster XL is a digital form of ISIS.And so, I recommend you save your dollar, and your time. Life is short, and you need not spend any of it on this child porn which masquerades as “Art.”Oh, and DON’T GIVE IN to the fact that the developer continues to update his game more than a year post-release, and even answers questions when players email him. Such behavior merely shows his inability to countenance the horror of this plague he’s unleashed on the world.So overall, I’d say it’s okay.5/10"
